{"id": 225000768, "title": "Seven-day warning as \u00a3500k National Lottery as prize still unclaimed in Redditch", "text": "The countdown is on to find a mystery National Lottery winner who has just over a week left to claim \u00a3500,000. The winner of the eye-watering Thunderball prize purchased a ticket in Redditch almost six months ago. The winner matched all five main numbers and the Thunderball in the draw on December 8, 2023. The numbers were 2, 15, 31, 35, 37 and the Thunderball was 6. The lottery player only has until June 5 to claim their top prize.Andy Carter of The National Lottery said: \u201cIt's been almost six months and we've still not been contacted by the rightful ticket-holder to claim their prize - despite numerous appeals. Read more: We visited Birmingham school where excluded kids are welcomed with open arms and offered a chance \"All hope is not lost, however. We\u2019ve received valid claims on major National Lottery unclaimed prizes right up to the very last minute before - but time is running out. \"It really is as simple as taking a couple of minutes out of your day to dig out and check your Thunderball tickets. We\u2019re urging everyone to double-check the pockets of clothing, in wallets, bags and down the back of the sofa for the missing ticket. \"This money could really make a huge difference to someone\u2019s life. We're ready and waiting with champagne on ice for that life-changing phone call to come in to us here at The National Lottery. \"Players can check their tickets online by downloading the National Lottery app or on our website. Players can also check tickets in retail. \"Playing online via the app or website means that your ticket is checked, and you get an email notification if you win a prize. You can also scan your retail tickets on the National Lottery app to check if you're a winner.\u201d If no-one claims the prize money before the deadline, the huge sum will go into helping National Lottery-funded projects across th